  "text": "Among HIV-infected patients studied, there might be significant variations in the duration of HIV infection and systemic viral burden, which might influence the development of CSVD as some investigators proposed that HIV might directly infect vascular smooth muscle cells [CITATION_1] . In our study, the estimated duration of HIV infection was not significantly associated with either mild or moderate/severe CSVD. Data on plasma viral load were not sufficient for analysis. Additionally, whether HIV infection per se conferred a greater risk of CSVD was not addressed in our study because the number of HIV-seronegative autopsy cases was insufficient for analysis.",
